(193, 2, '2013-03-30 22:22:26', '2013-03-30 22:22:26', 'You are here: <a title="View Home" href="http://students.umw.edu/studentactivities/">Home</a> / <a title="View Student Clubs and Organizations" href="http://students.umw.edu/studentactivities/student-clubs-and-organizations/">Student Clubs and Organizations</a> / List of Student Clubs\r\n<div>\r\n<h1>List of Student Clubs</h1>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<img alt="" src="http://students.umw.edu/studentactivities/files/2011/10/DayofSilence.jpg" width="538" height="257" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nClubs which are not officially recognized by the Inter-Club Association (ICA) are in<em> italics</em>.\r\n\r\nYou can also find information about registered clubs on <a href="https://orgsync.com/login/university-of-mary-washington">OrgSync.</a> Club Sports are listed at <a href="http://students.umw.edu/clubsports/sponsored-sport-clubs/">Campus Recreation</a>.\r\n\r\nPlease contact the Office of Student Activities and Engagement at <a href="mailto:osacs@umw.edu">sae@umw.edu</a> or 540- 654-1061 if you have any questions.  Faculty Advisors’ UMW phone extensions are in parenthesis (prefix with 1-540-654 if dialing from outside of the University).\r\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr align="left" valign="bottom">\r\n<th bgcolor="#f8f8f8">\r\n<div align="center">Club Name</div></th>\r\n<th width="50%">\r\n<div align="center">Description</div></th>\r\n<th bgcolor="#f8f8f8">\r\n<div align="center">Contact Information</div></th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">African Student Union\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59475/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The primary goal of the African Student Union is to spread awareness about the different African cultures. We strive to overcome stereotypes and create unity within our community. Our club also dedicates its time to support a variety of African charities.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:agetache@mail.umw.edu">Ayida Getachew</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:tande@mail.umw.edu">Taiwo Ande</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><a href="mailto:aikidoInn@aol.com">Aikido at UMW\r\n</a></td>\r\n<td>The purpose of Aikido is to teach students the act of Aikido, a martial art developed in Japan.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:dryer@mail.umw.edu">Daniel Ryer</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:lpenwell@umw.edu">Larry Penwell</a>(x1561)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><a href="http://alphamusigma.wordpress.com/" target="_blank">Alpha Mu Sigma (AMS) </a>\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/60360/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Alpha Mu Sigma is a local, social fraternity that strives to unite the Mary Washington community with a lifelong bond via community service and bonding activities.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:jburke2@mail.umw.edu">Jill Burke\r\n</a><strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:jmollo@umw.edu">Joe Mollo</a>(x1061)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Alter Egos Step Team\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59912/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Stepping is a type of dance that uses clapping and stomping that make unique beats to music.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:jholmes4@mail.umw.edu">Jeneka Holmes</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:msanford@umw.edu">Marion Sanford</a>(x1044)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><em>Alternative Spring Break</em></td>\r\n<td>Donate your spring break to a good cause with COAR!</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:srezazad@mail.umw.edu">Shayda Rezazad</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:ceggenbe@umw.edu">Christian Eggenberger</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><em>American Marketing Association</em></td>\r\n<td>We exist to enhance interested students’ knowledge about the marketing industry and careers.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:bcomfort@mail.umw.edu">Brooke Comfort</a>\r\n<a href="mailto:rcarroll@mail.umw.edu">Raven Carroll</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:ccreque@umw.edu">Carol Ann Creque</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Arabic Language Club\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59567/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>To promote the study of Arabic language and raise awareness of Arab customs and culture in the campus community.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:mgoodman@mail.umw.edu">Marjahn Goodman</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:naltakri@uwm.edu">Nabil Al-Takriti</a>(x1481)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Asian Student Association (ASA)\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59767/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The Asian Student Association seeks to promote the appreciation and understanding of Asia through social, educational and cultural activities. ASA is a unified student body that does not consist of members solely of Asian descent.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:gnoh@mail.umw.edu">Gina Noh\r\n</a><strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:khandley@umw.edu">Kevin Handley</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Association for Computing Machinery (ACM)\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59710/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The chapter is organized and will be operated exclusively for educational and scientific purposes to promote the increasing of knowledge of and greater interest in the science, design, development, construction, languages, management, and applications of modern computing, and as a means of communication between persons having an interest in computing.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:jwhite3@mail.umw.edu">Jessica White</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:stephen@umw.edu">Stephen Davies</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Association of Residence Halls (ARH)\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59519/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>ARH represents residential students on SGA and provides guidance to the residence hall councils.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:alieuran@mail.umw.edu">Alyssa Lieurance </a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:\r\n</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Aubade\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59512/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Aubade is the annual literary arts magazine. They seek to showcase the artistic and literary talents of UMW students.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:jrandal3@mail.umw.edu">Jenna Randall </a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:craffert@umw.edu">Colin Rafferty</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Baby Steps\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/63716/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Baby Steps aims to develop resources at UMW for parenting students and staff, and to foster an environment that supports such students and their families.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:cboucher@mail.umw.edu">Carly Boucher</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:stephen@umw.edu">Stephen Davies</a>(x1317)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><em>Baptist Collegiate Ministries</em></td>\r\n<td>College is a time of transformation. It’s a time to question. To learn. To grow. The BCM is a place where it’s safe to ask questions and to wrestle with what is good, true, and beautiful. It’s a place where all of the disparate parts of life are brought together and made whole. Will you join us? The campus minister can be contacted at <a href="mailto:Carey.Sims@vbmb.org">Carey.Sims@vbmb.org</a></td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:reiker@mail.umw.edu">Rachel Eiker </a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:stephen@umw.edu">Stephen Davies</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Baseball\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59451/chapter">OrgSync</a><em>\r\n</em></td>\r\n<td>Club sport for men seeking to play baseball competitively.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:mchrist2@mail.umw.edu">Mark Christiansen</a><strong>\r\nFaculty Advisor:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:mmermels@umw.edu">Mark Mermelstein</a><strong></strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Basketball (Men’s)</td>\r\n<td>Men’s Club Basketball is a group designed to deliver a competitive basketball atmosphere within the confines of the average college student.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:dritter@umw.edu">Alex Ritler </a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:myak@umw.edu">Melissa Yakabowki</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><a href="mailto:umwclubbaskeetball@gmail.com">Basketball (Women’s)</a>\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59469/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The club is for people who want a fun and competitive environment. We fundraise and volunteer in the Fredericksburg community.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:amiller2@mail.umw.edu">Alex Miller\r\n</a><strong>Faculty Advisor:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:mmermels@umw.edu">Mark Mermelstein</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><a href="mailto:battlefield@umw.edu">Battlefield Yearbook</a>\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59709/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The Battlefield provides the UMW students with a yearbook capturing the academic school year’s memories.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong><a href="mailto:kjames@mail.umw.edu">\r\nKarmel James</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:jmollo@umw.edu">Joe Mollo</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><em>BellA’capella\r\n</em><a href="https://orgsync.com/60002/chapter">OrgSync<em>\r\n</em></a></td>\r\n<td>BellACapella is an all girls A’capella singing group that has been around for over 10 years. We bring a wide array of songs from all genres to our campus.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:kpresere@mail.umw.edu">Katherine Preseren</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:dodell@umw.edu">Deborah O’Dell</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><a href="mailto:umwbestbuddies@aol.com"><em>Best Buddies</em></a>\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59707/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>College students are matched in one-to-one friendships with people in the community with intellectual and developmental disabilities and take part in group and individual activities.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:cdodrill@mail.umw.edu">Casey Dodrill </a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:vmackint@umw.edu">Virgina Mackintosh</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Biology Club\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59449/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Biology Club is meant to connect those who are biology majors or interested in biology to resources in the department and school to further their interest. It helps connect people who are majors to scientific opportunities inside and outside the university.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:sarahmccue92@gmail.com">Sarah McCue</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:jkillian@umw.edu">Joella Killian</a>(x1418)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Black Student Association (BSA)\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59570/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The purpose of our club is to try and bring together students of black descent and all races together and have a good time</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:rstovall@mail.umw.edu">Romadon Stovall </a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:msanford@umw.edu">Marion Sanford</a>(x1044)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Blue Tide Lacrosse (Men’s)\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59455/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>We are the men’s club lacrosse team, Blue Tide. Our purpose is to provide students with the opportunity to continue playing at a competitive level and advance their skills. All skill levels are welcomed and we are open to teaching the sport rules and regulations to players who are new to lacrosse.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:jkrzywic@mail.umw.edu">Joseph Krzywicki </a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:dpierand@mail.umw.edu">Dave Pierandi</a>(x1662)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Boxing\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/60039/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>UMW Boxing is for students to learn the basics and fundamentals of boxing, practice form and technique, and spar with one another.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:adecina@umw.edu">Alex Decina</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:Lpenwell@umw.edu">Larry Penwell</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Breakers</td>\r\n<td>Analyzing and practicing the art of break dancing, alongside other aspects of hip-hop.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:jyi@mail.umw.edu">Justin Yi</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:bmendez@umw.edu">Beverly Mendez</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Brothers of a New Direction (BOND)</td>\r\n<td>A club that promotes brotherhood through unity and togetherness; in the end we all come together as one.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:rstovall@mail.umw.edu">Romadon Stovall</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong>\r\nMarion Sanford</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">The Bullet\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59518/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The Bullet is the University of Mary Washington’s student-run newspaper. It provides the UMW community with campus, local, national and world news, as well as editorials, sports and entertainment.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:wbowman@mail.umw.edu">Thomas Bowman</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:mmccart2@umw.edu">Michael McCarthy</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><a href="mailto:umwclasscouncil@gmail.com">Class Council </a>\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/50826/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Class Council coordinates and maintains all traditional class-wide events. Our non-profit organization functions as a separate entity from Student Government Association. The intention of Class Council is to provide inexpensive social activities for the student body.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:jcrystle@mail.umw.edu">Jennifer Crystle</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:mhiggin3@umw.edu">Megan Higginbotham</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><a href="http://cccumw.wordpress.com/"><em>Campus Christian Community (CCC)</em></a>\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/62554/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Welcoming all people, the CCC ministers with students, faculty and staff at the University of Mary Washington through worship, fellowship and service, and provides a forum to explore questions of faith and life.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:sdavis2@mail.umw.edu">Sarah Davis</a>\r\n<a href="mailto:estorey@mail.umw.edu">Elizabeth Storey</a>\r\n<strong>Facultuy Advisor:</strong>\r\nJoe Mollo</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Campus Scouts\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59723/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Campus Scouts is group that volunteers with local scouting groups in the Fredericksburg area by planning educational events, helping with cookie sales, and mentoring scouts of all ages.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:kgibson@mail.umw.edu">Kate Gibson\r\n</a><strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:jwilson@umw.edu">Joni Wilson</a>(x2088)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><a href="http://umwcanterbury.com/"><em>Canterbury Club</em></a></td>\r\n<td>Canterbury is a campus ministry geared towards students from the Episcopal/Anglican and Lutheran traditions, although we welcome students of other Christian backgrounds. We strive to be an open, inclusive and questioning community of faith for students who are seeking to follow Christ while at college.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:tpoindex@mail.umw.edu">Taylor Poindexter</a>\r\n<strong>Facultuy Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:dodell@umw.edu">Deborah O’Dell</a>(x1417)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><em>Catholic Campus Ministries\r\n</em><a href="https://orgsync.com/59594/chapter">OrgSync<em>\r\n</em></a></td>\r\n<td>Catholic Campus Ministry is organized by the Catholic students of the University of Mary Washington, in conjunction with the Catholic Diocese of Arlington. The CCM’s mission is to provide a sound Roman Catholic spiritual center for the students, staff, and faculty at UMW. Our goal is to apply the Gospel of Our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ in all of our activities.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:tfrelk@mail.umw.edu">Tracy Frelk\r\n</a><strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:elarus@umw.edu">Elizabeth Larus</a>(x1497)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Cheap Seats Cinema\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59492/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Cheap Seats strives to bring quality film entertainment to the UMW community with block buster movies on campus for a low fee of $1. Movies are shown almost every weekend in Monroe 116.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:adamergis.umw.edu">Angela Damergis</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:jmollo@umw.edu">Joe Mollo</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Cheerleading\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59450/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The goal of the UMW Cheerleading Club is to promote school spirit by cheering for men’s and women’s varsity basketball. We hold practice three times each week during which we work to improve our cheerleading skills in a fun, supportive, friendly but also challenging environment. All skill levels are welcome to join us in supporting the “Eagle Nation”</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:kellis3@mail.umw.edu">Kimberly Ellis</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:mmermels@umw.edu">Mark Mermelstein</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><a href="mailto:umwcot@gmail.com">Children of Time</a>\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/62602/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The purpose of COT is to look at the science fiction of the modern word: how it depicts possible futures, the metaphors for modern issues that we deal every day, and the issues we have dealt with in the past.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:rhill2@mail.umw.edu">Robert Hill </a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:jromero@umw.edu">Joseph Romero</a>(x1340)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><a href="http://umwcirclekinternational.umwblogs.org/">Circle K International</a>\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59595/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Circle K is the college level of Key Club. We are a tight-knit, enthusiastic community service club focused on our three tenants of leadership, fellowship and service.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:kgriffit@mail.umw.edu">Kelly Griffith</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong><a href="mailto:mmira@umw.edu">\r\nMarisa Martinez-Mira</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Civil War Reenactors Club</td>\r\n<td>We are a club that participates in re-enacting histories and battles. We interpret history to the public through re-enacting and we go to many battlefields and historical sites.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:sredmile@umw.edu">Sean Redmiles</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:kmoon@umw.edu">Krystyn Moon</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Classics Club\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59514/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Classics Club meets to discuss and enjoy classical languages and history. We are interested in anything to do with Ancient Classical Civilizations such as Greece and Rome.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:atkblad@mail.umw.edu">Ana Tkabladze</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:jromero@umw.edu">Joseph Romero</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">College Republicans</td>\r\n<td>The College Republicans support local Republican candidates for office and meet to discuss current events.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:ebrennan@mail.umw.edu">Elizabeth Brennan</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:lfrackte@umw.edu">Leigh Frackelton</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Commuter Student Association\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/60282/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The Commuter Student Association (CSA) is an official UMW organization dedicated to serving the needs of the commuter student population.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:ablanck@mail.umw.edu">Ally Blanck</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:cporter@umw.edu">Chris Porter</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Dance Team</td>\r\n<td>The UMW Dance Team promotes school spirit by perfomring at school functions, pep rallies, home basketball games, and Homecoming.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:agrassel@mail.umw.edu">Anne Grasselli</a>\r\n<a href="mailto:Gquirey@mail.umw.edu">Gaelyn Quirey</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:cmurphy3@umw.edu">Chad Murphey</a>(x1061)<strong>\r\n</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Dodgeball Club</td>\r\n<td>The Dodgeball Club’s primary function is to organize and fund dodgeball games open to everyone two to three times a week outside of Bushnell in the basketball cage. In addition, we will travel to compete in dodgeball tournaments, and host tournaments with proceeds going to charity.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:Ipotere@mail.umw.edu">Ian Potere\r\n</a><strong>Faculty Advisor:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:mpearson@umw.edu">Michael Pearson </a><strong>\r\n</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Eagle Bhangra</td>\r\n<td>Eagle Bhangra contributes meaningfully to the diversity experience at UMW. This organization is a performance team that appeals to students of all cultures that are interested in the dance, dress, and dynamic present of Bhangra’s South Asian and Central Asian roots.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:ukapoor@mail.umw.edu">Upma Kapoor</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:\r\n</strong>Smita Jain Oxford (x1454)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><em>Eagle Nation</em></td>\r\n<td>Eagle Nation is a spirit committee devoted to showing the student support of various activities ranging from athletic events to Mary Washington fundraisers.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:dcarpent@mail.umw.edu">David Carpenter</a>\r\n<a href="mailto:kvanvalk@mail.umw.edu">Katie Sue Van Valkenburg</a><strong>\r\nFaculty Advisor:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:ktomlin@umw.edu">Kim Tomlin</a>(x1061)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Ecology Club\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59484/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Our meetings are every Thursday at 8:00 pm in Lee Hall Room 412. Once a month we will be attending the local Sierra Club meetings instead of having general meetings.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:scorron2@mail.umw.edu">Samantha Corron</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:mszulcze@umw.edu">Melanie Szulczeuski</a>(x2345)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Enigma Colorguard\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59452/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>We combine dance with spinning flags, rifles and sabres, and put it to music to tell a story.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:nerickso@mail.umw.edu">Nicole Erickson</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:bmendez@umw.edu">Beverly Mendez</a>(x1243)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Economics Club</td>\r\n<td>The UMW Economics Club is a club open to all UMW students which holds enjoyable economics-related events.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:myoder@mail.umw.edu">Marissa Yoder</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:shumphre@umw.edu">Shawn Humphrey</a>(x1487)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><em>Encore\r\n</em><a href="https://orgsync.com/63695/chapter">OrgSync<em>\r\n</em></a></td>\r\n<td>We are a show choir performance club. Our goal is to promote UMW spirit through a mutual love of music and dance.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:cgauthie@mail.umw.edu">Catherine Gauthier</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:bmendez@umw.edu">Beverly Mendez</a>(x1317)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><em>Encounter\r\n</em><a href="https://orgsync.com/60009/chapter">OrgSync<em>\r\n</em></a></td>\r\n<td>Encounter exists to help students come in contact with biblical truth and biblical community with a real life application. It is working in association with Spotswood Baptist Church.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:sbattles@umw.edu">Stephanie Battleson</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:sdavis@umw.edu">Stephen Davies</a>(x1317)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">ELC Club\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/64132/chapter">OrgSync<em></em></a></td>\r\n<td>Our purpose as a club is to create a connection within the ELC community, through establishing bonds between the students and faculty, via a monthly Q and A series, trips to book readings downtown and within the state, visits to performances in DC/on campus, opportunities to network with alumni, in hopes of establishing a solid community of language lovers.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:\r\n</strong>Tonto Duncan<strong>\r\nFaculty Advisor:</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Feminists United On Campus\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/63432/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>This club is about equality, the exchange of information, work in the community, and the celebration of feminism!</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:atruslow@mail.umw.edu">Annie Truslow</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\nTracy Citeroni\r\n<a href="mailto:ckilmart@umw.edu">Chris Kilmartin</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><a href="http://fencing.umwblogs.org/">Mary Washington Fencing Club</a>\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59568/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>MW Fencing teaches students how to compete in the Olympic sport of fencing in a friendly environment The club welcomes all level of experience and will also provide equipment. En garde!</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:jstockto@mail.umw.edu">Jenna Stockton\r\n</a><strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:zwhalen@umw.edu">Zach Whalen</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Field Hockey\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59578/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Club Field Hockey is an organization that provides the opportunity for any student to have a fun time playing field hockey and competing with other universities.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:abruce@mail.umw.edu">Ashley Bruce</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor</strong>:\r\n<a href="mailto:ktomlin@mail.umw.edu">Kim Tomlin</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Finance Committee</td>\r\n<td>Finance Committee allocates funds to ICA Clubs on campus.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:mdelacruz49@gmail.com">Monique Dela Cruz</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor</strong>:\r\n<a href="mailto:jmollo@umw.edu">Joe Mollo</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Future Business Leaders of America (FBLA)\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59489/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>FBLA is an opportunity for students to get more involved with the business major. We help clubs market on campus, host leadership activities, and volunteer.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:kkutnak@mail.umw.edu">Kathleen Kutnak</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong><a href="mailto:dhubbard@umw.edu">\r\n</a><a href="mailto:dhubbard@umw.edu">Dan Hubbard</a>(x1460)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><em>The Gathering\r\n</em><a href="https://orgsync.com/60007/chapter">OrgSync<em>\r\n</em></a></td>\r\n<td>An on-campus, non-denominational Bible study led by an awesome local pastor. Each semester we do an in-depth study of one book of the Bible, seeking to gain a deeper understanding of God’s word and how we can apply it to our lives.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:gcohen@mail.umw.edu">Gemma Cohen</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:stephen@umw.edu">Stephen Davies</a>(x1317)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Geography Club</td>\r\n<td>Spreading the love and knowledge of all things Geography!</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:dchamber@mail.umw.edu">David Chambers</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:jgallagh@umw.edu">Jackie Gallagher</a>(x1493)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">German Club\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/62535/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>UMW German Club’s purpose is to promote the German language and culture in a fun and educational way.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:kwilson3@mail.umw.edu">Kelsey Wilson</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:mrotter@umw.edu">Marcel Rotter</a>(x1996)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Giant Productions\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/50633/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Giant Productions is in charge of bringing entertainment to UMW – comedians, musicians, etc. Giant books events and so students can have a great time. From the meetings Giant decides what the campus most wants to see and tries to make it happen. Giant brings as much entertainment as possible while making it as accessible as possible.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:lsouthal@mail.umw.edu">Lonnie Southall\r\n</a><strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:jmollo@umw.edu">Joe Mollo</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Historic Preservation Club\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/60116/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The purpose of the Historic Preservation Club is to promote preservation to our majors, the campus community, and downtown Fredericksburg. We strive to educate club members and others on up to date preservation issues through many different venues</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:susparm@gmail.com">Susanna Parmelee\r\n</a><strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong><a href="mailto:gstanton@umw.edu">\r\nGary Stanton</a>(x1313)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Honor Council\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59487/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Educating and upholding honor throughout the campus and beyond.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:alarmour@mail.umw.edu">Zandi Larmour</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:dsearcy@umw.edu">Doug Searcy</a>(x1062)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Humans vs. Zombies Club\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59592/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The purpose of Humans vs. Zombies is to engage in team work, to create deep bonds between players, to foster communication between teammates and other players, and to create strategies based on missions and obstacles. Humans vs. Zombies is a game of moderated tag played at schools across the world. Human players must remain vigilant and defend themselves with socks and Nerf guns to avoid being tagged by a growing zombie horde.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:ecoxe@mail.umw.edu">Eileen Coxe</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong><a href="mailto:ebonds@umw.edu">\r\nEric Bonds</a>(x1436)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Inter-Club Association</td>\r\n<td>We advice and oversee all ICA-approved clubs.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong><strong>\r\nFaculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:jmollo@umw.edu">Joe Mollo</a>(x1061)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><a href="mailto:ivmclub@gmail.com"><em>InterVarsity Christian Fellowship</em></a>\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/62538/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>IV is an inter-denominational Christian fellowship, pursuing Christ’s gift of love and salvation on the UMW campus. We are a group passionately devoted to Jesus, and sharing him with the world.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:bapelqui@mail.umw.edu">Bethany Apelquist</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:sstagebe@umw.edu">Stephen Stageberg</a>(x1486)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Invisible Children\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59556/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Invisible Children raises awareness about Africa’s longest running civil war, as well as raising funds for relief projects on the ground.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:spreston@mail.umw.edu">Stephanie Preston</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:elarus@umw.edu">Elizabeth Larus (x1497)</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Islamic Student Association (ISA)\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59575/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The purpose of ISA shall be to raise cultural awareness of Islam and Islamic culture, to widen and increase the knowledge of young people in Islam, to be a visible presence on the UMW campus, and to serve those in need in our community.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:azafar@mail.umw.edu">Aqsa Zafar\r\n</a><strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:maminraz@umw.edu">Medhi Aminrazavi</a>(x1341)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Japanese Animated and Dramatic Entertainment (J.A.D.E.)\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/60005/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The purpose of J.A.D.E. is to showcase the cultural variety of Japanese animated entertainment, as well as to provide a forum where Japanese history, language, art, myths, games, and music can be discussed and enjoyed.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:abeichle@mail.umw.edu">Andrew Beichler\r\n</a><strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:kmcclusk@umw.edu">Kevin McClusky</a>(x1979)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Jewish Student Association / Hillel (JSA)\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59476/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Our mission is to promote Jewish life on Mary Washington’s campus through both cultural and religious activities. Further, we aim to add to the overall diversity of Mary Washington’s student body by promotion tolerance, communication, and education.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact: </strong><a href="mailto:tharpert@mail.umw.edu">\r\n</a><a href="mailto:hfeingol@mail.umw.edu">Hallie Feingold\r\n</a><a href="mailto:zfeinste@mail.umw.edu">Zach Feinstein </a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:dretting@mail.umw.edu">David Rettinger</a>(x1364)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><a href="http://judicial.umwblogs.org/">Judicial Review Board (JRB)</a></td>\r\n<td>The Judicial Review Boardhandles judicial matters on campus dealing with minor student policy violations.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:ebrennan@mail.umw.edu">Elizabeth Brennan</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:rtuttle@umw.edu">Ray Tuttle </a>(x1527)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><a href="mailto:umwclublax@gmail.com">Lacrosse Club (Women’s)</a></td>\r\n<td>Cool girls. Cool lacrosse. Cool.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:Kselby@gmail.com">Kandra Selby</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:mmathews@umw.edu">Mary Beth Mathews</a> (x1354)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Latin Dance Club\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59491/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The Latin Dance Club teaches interested students how to dance common Latino dances such as salsa, merengue, and bachata.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:ematute@umw.edu">Elizabeth Matute</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:mmira@umw.edu">Marisa Martinez Mira</a> (x1986)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Latino Student Assocation (LSA)\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59585/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>To expose and enhance Latino-American culture at UMW through celebration, volunteerism and support for students and residents alike from every background, ethnicity and age.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:mfloresv@mail.umw.edu">Mayra Flores-Valderde</a><a href="mailto:omedina@umw.edu">\r\n</a><strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:mbocazle@umw.edu">Maria Laura Bocaz</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Master Plan Awareness Club</td>\r\n<td>(Impact) – Our goal is to inform students about the changes on campus related to the master plan for the purposes of inviting discussion, celebrating campus history and inspiring future alumni to bond with the landscape.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:gcorkill@mail.umw.edu">Gwendolyn Corkill</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:gstull@umw.edu">Gregg Stull</a>(x1980)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Mathematical Association of America, UMW Student Chapter\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59479/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The MAA student group works closely with faculty, mathematics majors, and any mathematically-inclined students in hosting activities advancing interest in all aspects of mathematics. The student group of the MAA is affiliated with the national office of the Mathematical Association of America, a professional organization which includes university faculty and students of all levels.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:cbenshof@mail.umw.edu">Candice Bensoff</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:rhelmstu@umw.edu">Randall Helmstutler</a>(x1329)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">MedLife\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/64133/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Our mission is to help families achieve greater freedom from the constraints of poverty, empowering them to live healthier lives. Our patients did not choose to be poor, but they have chosen to strive toward a better life; MEDLIFE stands beside them in this pursuit.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:\r\n</strong>Marco Montero\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Mock Trial Team</td>\r\n<td>UMW’s Mock Trial team competes in college mock trial competitions organized by the American Mock Trial Association. Each year, AMTA releases a criminal or civil case. UMW’s Mock Trial Team prepares a defense case, a prosecution case, and witnesses for each side. At each competition UMW’s prosecution competes against the defense team of other schools and vice versa. In the 2011-2012 competition year UMW’s Mock Trial team ranked high enough at the Regional Tournament to go on to the first round of the Championships.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:atraore@mail.umw.edu">Aissata Traore</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:storr@lawyers-virginia.com">Ghislaine Storr Burks</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><a href="http://umwmun.umwblogs.org/">Model United Nations</a>\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59511/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Model UN is an organization of students with an interest in politics, history, diplomacy, and international issues. We attend several college conferences annually to debate real United Nations concerns, as well as win awards. We practice debate, writing and research skills in a fun, dynamic setting.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:ccherico@mail.umw.edu">Courtney Cherico</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:jdavidso@mail.umw.edu">Jason Davidson</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><a href="mailto:umw.nscs@gmail.com"><em>National Society of Collegiate Scholars</em></a>\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/60004/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>NSCS is a student honor society dedicated to leadership and community service. NSCS holds many charity events and hosts spirit weeks. It is an active on-campus presence to members and non-members alike.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:hlehnen@mail.umw.edu">Hanna Lehnen</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:rtuttle@umw.edu">Ray Tuttle</a>(x1660)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">No Labels at UMW\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/63058/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>No Labels is a national bipartisan organization committed to fighting against the growing divide in our government between Republicans and Democrats. Our congressional and presidential reforms are designed to encourage our leaders to compromise and stop the ongoing issues within the legislature.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:aturner2@mail.umw.edu">Camille Turner</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:sfarmswo@umw.edu">Stephen Farnsworth</a>(x11404)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><em>New Life College Connection</em></td>\r\n<td>College Connection is a ministry of New Life in Christ Church. We are a Christian community for the “convinced” and the “unconvinced.” College Connection is a place where students can ask hard questions about Christianity and grow in their understanding of Christian life.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:cbender@mail.umw.edu">Caroline Bender</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:cgarcia@umw.edu">Christopher Garcia</a> (x1456)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Object Manipulation Group (OMG)\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/60006/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The purpose of OMG is to promote and advance the art of juggling, hooping, and other forms of object manipulation.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:omgofumw@gmail.com">Anna Penniman</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:kmachand@umw.edu">Kenneth Machande</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><a href="http://www.onenotestand.com/">The One Note Stand</a>\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/60094/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>One Note Stand is a co-ed A Cappella group that provides the UMW campus and surrounding community with student arranged music covering genres from pop to oldies, hip hop, jazz, indie, choral, original music, and more.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:rweiss@mail.umw.edu">Regina Weiss</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:pgriggs@umw.edu">Paul Griggs</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Operation Smile</td>\r\n<td>Operation Smile is a non-profit, international organization with the goal to provide cleft palette operations on impoverished children. Through weekly fundraising events, UMW’s Operation Smile chapter hopes to raise awareness of the group’s cause, while concurrently making monetary contributions.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:badams2@mail.umw.edu">Brandee Adams</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:ncrowder@umw.edu">K. Nicole Crowder</a> (x1016)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Orpheum Film Club\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59557/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Orpheum seeks to both educate and entertain the students of UMW by screening and discussing classic, independent, and foreign films. The aim is to broaden perspectives by exposing students to films that might otherwise be overlooked.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:mboyle@mail.umw.edu">Margaret Boyle </a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:lkoos@umw.edu">Leonard Koos</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><a href="http://outdoor.umwblogs.org/">Outdoor Club</a>\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59587/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Outdoors Club is geared towards group outings that are organized by the club officers. Our trips include kayaking, canoeing, rock climbing, hiking, camping and rafting.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:cpsaltis@mail.umw.edu">Caroline Psaltis\r\n</a><strong>Faculty Advisor:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:jlaroche@umw.edu">Jeremy Larochelle (x1368)\r\n</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Paws\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/60008/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Paws is an organization that combines an interest group for animal lovers with an opportunity to volunteer at adoptions and shelters.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:nmight@mail.umw.edu">Natalie Might </a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:dbaker2@umw.edu">Dianne Baker</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><a href="http://prismblog.umwblogs.org/">People for the Rights of Individuals of Sexual Minorities</a>(PRISM)\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59513/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The purpose of PRISM is to promote the value of diversity and acceptance of students of sexual and gender minorities and allies of the GLBTTQQIAAP community through club meetings and sponsored events on campus.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:kristen.ashley.lamb@gmail.com">Kristen Lamb\r\n</a><strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:grichard@umw.edu">Gary Richards</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><a href="http://umwpac.umwblogs.org/">Performing Arts Club\r\n</a><a href="https://orgsync.com/59576/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The Performing Arts Club offers performance, choreography, and leadership opportunities in dance. PAC dancers hold two shows each semester and offer workshops and other performance opportunities.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:clewandr@mail.umw.edu">Courtney Lewandrowski</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:bmendez@umw.edu">Beverly Mendez</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">PERL\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59482/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>PERL strives to promote, encourage, recruit, and lead women in technology and computer science as well as promote unity within the computer science department.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:bakers@mail.umw.edu">Bethany Akers</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:stephen@umw.edu">Stephen Davies</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Pre-Medical / Pre-Dental Club\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59485/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The goal of UMW’s Pre-Medicine/Pre-Dental Clubis to foster the desire of UMW students to provide service to those in our community while pursuing a career in healthcare.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:rgreen3@mail.umw.edu">Ryan Green</a>\r\n<a href="mailto:adamergi@mail.umw.edu">Angela Damergis</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:sgalllik@umw.edu">Stephen G. Gallik</a>(x1419)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Physical Therapy and Occupational Therapy Club</td>\r\n<td>Provide information to students interested in becoming physical therapists or occupational therapists. We provide outlines of the recommended classes and schedule admissions directors of various schools to visit UMW.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:kdeppe@mail.umw.edu">Kelsey Deppe</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:dodell@umw.edu">Deborah O’Dell</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Pre-Vet Club</td>\r\n<td>The Pre-Vet Club provides those interested in a veterinary career or other animal related careers with application advice, course advise, and volunteer opportunities.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:kmonti@mail.umw.edu">Katelynn Monti\r\n</a><strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:llewis@umw.edu">Lynn Lewis</a>(x1415)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Renaissance Club\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59483/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The Mary Washington Renaissance Club is devoted to the enthusiastic preservation and recreation of historical customs during the Renaissance period.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:ktarr@mail.umw.edu">Kathryn Tarr</a><a href="mailto:ngiangre@mail.umw.edu">\r\n</a><strong>Faculty Advisor:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:tkennedy@umw.edu">Theresa Kennedy</a>(x1531)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Rotaract Club</td>\r\n<td>Rotaract Club is a service club for the Fredericksburg and Stafford community. Subset of the Rotary Club</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:cragghia@mail.umw.edu">Casey Ragghianti </a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:dschleef@umw.edu">Debra Schleef</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Rugby Club (Men’s)\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59911/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>We have been around for over 30 years. There are no cuts, so everyone plays. We are a traveling sport that gives opportunity to play competitive rugby and have fun,</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:mmcaloon@mail.umw.edu">Matt McAloon</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:mspen1bi@umw.edu">Michael Spencer</a>(x1311)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><a href="http://www.marywashwomensrugby.com/">Rugby Club (Women)</a>\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59569/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>UMW Women’s Rugby was established in 1985. Since then the club has achieved great success. The season for Women’s Rugby includes both fall and spring semesters with games traditionally held on Saturdays; tournaments are sometimes held on Saturdays and Sundays. Practice is held MWF afternoons from 4pm to 6pm at Hanover Recreation Field.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:lhampson@umw.edu">Lara Hampson</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:mmermels@umw.edu">Mark Mermelstein</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Scuba Club\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/62603/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>A club for students to come together and share their interest in scuba diving.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:lcastell@umw.edu">Lauren Castello\r\n</a><strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:ntibert@umw.edu">Neil Tilbert</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Ski and Snowboard\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59474/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>A ski and snowboard club for all abilities, seeking powder wherever it falls.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:Dchamber@mail.umw.edu">David Chambers</a>\r\n<a href="mailto:rjarvis@mail.umw.edu">Rob Jarvis</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:jromero@umw.edu">Joseph Romero</a>(x0989)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Soccer (Men’s)\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59911/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Playing soccer in a less competitive environment, while having fun.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:knero@mail.umw.edu">Kyle Nero</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\nMark Mermelstein</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Soccer (Women’s)\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/50827/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>UMW Women’s Club Soccer competes in two outdoor seasons and one indoor season each year. We train and play matches in both the spring and fall, and compete indoors to keep our skills sharp in the winter. We practice on Monday, Wednesday and Friday afternoons and play games against other schools in our region on the weekends. We are a competitive team and require commitment and dedication, but anyone is welcome to play with us! Our main goals are improving as a team and just having fun, with outings for ice cream and team dinners. If you lovve to play the game and want to play soccer at a higher level, please contact us!</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:gchriste@mail.umw.edu">Grace Christenson</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\nMark Mermelstein</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Society of Pre-Law\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/60010/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The Society of Pre-Law is a student organization for those interested in the field of law. Our purpose is to network, prepare, and surround ourselves with other students interested in pursuing legal work.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:cchamber@mail.umw.edu">Chelsea Chamberlain</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:lfrackel@umw.edu">R. Leigh Frackelton</a>(x1452)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Society of Physics Students\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/60268/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The Society of Physics Students aims to teach, remind, and explore physics through on and off campus lectures, experiments, and workshops. There are activities for majors and non-majors alike.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:lnelson@mail.umw.edu">Lauren Nelson</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:gking@umw.edu">George King</a>(x1432)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Sociology and Anthropology Society\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59478/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The Sociology and Anthropology Society (also called Culture Club) provides a social forum for students interested in these disciplines to meet and explore related issues.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:pmccloy@mail.umw.edu">Patricia McCloy</a>\r\n<a href="mailto:ldick@mail.umw.edu">Laura Dick</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:egable@umw.edu">Eric Gable</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">UMW Club Softball\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59517/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The UMW Club Softball team is an all female undergrad student club that provides the opportunity for full-time students to play competitive softball against other club school teams. It welcomes students at all skill levels.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong></strong><strong>Student Contact:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:chicks@mail.umw.edu">Candice Hicks</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:tkennedy@umw.edu">Theresa Kennedy</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">UMW Street Hockey Club\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59516/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Pick up street hockey. No skating required. We welcome anyone with any level of experience.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:csmeeth@mail.umw.edu">Conan Smeeth</a><strong>\r\nFaculty Advisor:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:ntilbert@umw.edu">Neil Tilbert</a>(x1423)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><em>Student Anti-Violent Educators (SAVE)\r\n</em><a href="https://orgsync.com/60024/chapter">OrgSync<em>\r\n</em></a></td>\r\n<td>SAVE works to educate the student body about relationships and signs of healthy and unhealthy relationships. We host the Red Flag Campaign and the White Ribbon Campaign.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:mholbro2@umw.edu">Meagan Holbrook </a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:rtuttle@umw.edu">Ray Tuttle</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Student Art Association</td>\r\n<td>To promote and support student art on campus and in the Fr3edericksburg community</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:mattsonfields@gmail.com">Mattson Fields </a>\r\n<a href="http://students.umw.edu/studentactivities/student-clubs-and-organizations/list-of-student-clubs/emily@nicolaides.com">Emily Nicolaides</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:jmcmilla@umw.edu">J. McMillan</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Student Education Association (SEA)\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59486/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The SEA is a local chapter of the student Virginia Education Association, a pre-professional organization for future teachers, affiliated with the Virginia Education Association.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:vdrogo@mail.umw.edu">Valerie Drogo</a>\r\n<strong>Advisor: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:dwright@umw.edu">Dale Wright</a>(x1351)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Students Educating and Empowering for Diversity (SEED)\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59477/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>To raise awareness on campus about diversity and other cultures through workshops and residential facilitation.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:mgoodman@mail.umw.edu">Marjahn Goodman</a>\r\n<strong>Advisor: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:dnrallis@umw.edu">Donald Rallis</a>(x1492)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Students For Life</td>\r\n<td>Students for Life’s primary goal is to provide an educational forum for students and faculty regarding the issue of abortion and to provide opportunities for activism in the pro-life movement.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact: </strong><a href="mailto:jwood3@mail.umw.edu">\r\nJulia Wood\r\n</a><strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:elarus@umw.edu">Elizabeth Larus</a>(x1497)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><a href="http://sga.umw.edu/">Student Government Association (SGA)</a>\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59471/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The SGA is a forum where students bring their concerns about campus issues ranging from academics to safety. We are the students’ link with the administration.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:jthomps4@mail.umw.edu">Jeremy Thompson</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:crucker@umw.edu">Cedric Rucker</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><a href="http://www.studentshelpinghonduras.org/">Students Helping Honduras</a> (SHH)</td>\r\n<td>SHH has grown to encompass thousands of committed students from chapters at college campuses across the country. Under a growing body of leadership, SHH has brought hundreds of student volunteers to Honduras since its inception. SHH will continue to work with the poorest communities in Honduras to show that students CAN make a difference.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:pemsley@mail.umw.edu">Patrick Emsley</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:shumphre@umw.edu">W. Shawn Humphrey</a>(x1487)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Student Hip Hop Organization</td>\r\n<td>SHHO strives to promote higher learning through hip-hop. The organization has selectively worked with the best up-and-coming artists, hip hop legends, like minded companies, and passionate student talents – all who have established SHHO as an organic uncompromising brand.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:mthomas2@mail.umw.edu">Malik Thomas </a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:msanford@umw.edu">Marion Sanford</a>(x1044)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Students with Disabilities And Their Allies (SDATA)\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59546/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>SDATA is a club at UMW open to all students and faculty with or without a disability. The mission of the club is to promote fair treatment, tolerance, and acceptance of disabled students by engaging the community in disability-related issues through awareness and learning.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:ndobson@mail.umw.edu">Nicole Dobson</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:cfoss@umw.edu">Chris Foss</a> (x1128)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Swim Club\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/62537/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Swim Club is for new and old swimmers to exercise and compete together, as well as bond outside of the pool.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:cjohnso8@mail.umw.edu">Charlotte Johnson</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:mmermels@umw.edu">Mark Mermelstein</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Swing Dance Club\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59470/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The Swing Dance Club’s purpose is to bring swing dancing to the UMW campus and teach anyone who wants to learn.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:knelson2@mail.umw.edu">Kathleen Nelson\r\n</a><strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:mrigsby@umw.edu">Mary Rigsby</a>(x1540)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><a href="http://www.wix.com/umwsymfonics/umwsymfonics">Symfonics</a>\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59933/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Symfonics is UMW’s oldest co-ed A Cappella group. We arrange and sing a variety of music and are always excited to perform in, and out, of the Mary Washington community!</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:mgetz@mail.umw.edu">Melissa Getz\r\n</a><strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:jjames@umw.edu">Jason James</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Talk to the Hands Club\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59481/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Talk to the Hands is a club for UMW students, faculty and alumni interested in American Sign Language and deaf culture.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:ricard@mail.umw.edu">Rachel Icard\r\n</a><strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:dhubbard@umw.edu">Dan Hubbard</a>(x1460)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Tennis Club\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59454/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>UMW Club Tennis strives to maintain and enhance tennis skills in a fun, competitive, team-building environment at college. We play many schools in the state of Virginia and Maryland throughout the year. We have also gotten to the National Championships for the past two years.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:crieve@mail.umw.edu">Chris Rieve </a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:dpaitric@umw.edu">Don Paitrick</a>(x2483)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Terrapins Synchronized Swimming Team\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/60003/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The purpose of the Terrapins is to compete in synchronized swimming, as well as bringing the sport into the awareness of the greater public.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:jensustar@yahoo.com">Jennifer Sustar</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:mscanlon@umw.edu">Mara Scanlon</a>(x1544)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Two Dollar Challenge\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59515/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The Two Dollar Challenge is dedicated to involving students in awareness and action against poverty, including through challenge week, a fundraising and awareness-raising tool.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:esherma2@mail.umw.edu">Emily Sherman</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:professor.humphery@gmail.com">Shawn Humphrey</a>(x1487)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Ultimate Frisbee (Men’s)\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/60001/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Men’s Ultimate competes with other schools in the sport of Ultimate Frisbee.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:dlederle@mail.umw.edu">Dylan Lederle-Ensign</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:hnguyen@umw.edu">Hai Nguyen</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Ultimate Frisbee (Women)\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59558/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Women’s Ultimate’s main goal is to be competitive within USAU’s Division III pool of competition. We strive to achieve this by practicing our technical skills, promoting spirit of the game, and building team cohesion.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:ddavis3@mail.umw.edu">Devon Davis </a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:stephen@umw.edu">Stephen Davies</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">UNICEF</td>\r\n<td>UNICEF USA is an international organization dedicated to the “believe in zero.” 21,000 children die each day from preventable deaths, and the UNICEF mission is to make that number zero. The purpose of this club is to fundraiser for the children, educate the community, and advocate for children of other countries.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:elufumpa@mail.uwm.edu">Eniya Lufumpa</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:rsingh@umw.edu">Ranjit Singh</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><em>The Undeniably Adjacent</em></td>\r\n<td>The Undeniably Adjacent performs free, bi-monthly improv shows for the students and faculty of University of Mary Washington.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:matsonfields@gmail.com">Mattson Fields</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:shampton@umw.edu">Steve Hampton</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><em>University Programming Council (UPC)\r\n</em><a href="https://orgsync.com/59447/chapter">OrgSync<em>\r\n</em></a></td>\r\n<td>UPC programs all the events in the Underground, from weekly events to large scale event that take over Lee Hall.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:mandybuck91@gmail.com">Amanda Buckner</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a title="Joe" href="mailto:jmollo@umw.edu">Joe Mollo</a>(x1061)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><em>Unitarian Universalists\r\n</em><a href="https://orgsync.com/59593/chapter">OrgSync<em>\r\n</em></a></td>\r\n<td>UMW Unitarian Universalists promote tolerance, diversity, and education by providing safe and open-minded religious discussion and fellowship on campus, for both students familiar with Unitarian Universalism and people of other faiths.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:kcasey@mail.umw.edu">Katie Casey\r\n</a><strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:dschleef@umw.edu">Debra Schleef</a>(x1505)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Vegetarian Society</td>\r\n<td>A club for vegetarians, vegans, and anyone interested in helping animals. Our goals include maintaining a strong vegetarian presence on campus, raising money for animal rights groups, and encouraging discussion about animal rights issues.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:kodea@mail.umw.edu">Kat O’Dea\r\n</a><strong>Faculty Advisor:\r\n</strong>Paul Messplay</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Video Game Club\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/61171/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td> The club holds weekly meetings where members bring in their own video games and equipment for other members and themselves to play with. We also hold discussions about video games, embrace video game culture, and do video game-related events as well. Our meeting place is Monroe 211 every Saturday, 8p.m. to 11p.m.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:dlipsco2@mail.umw.edu">Daniel Lipscomb\r\n</a><strong>Faculty Advisor:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:zwhalen@umw.edu">Zach Whalen</a>(x2355)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Virginia Organizing</td>\r\n<td>Virginia Organizing is a statewide grassroots organization dedicated to challenging injustice by empowering people in local communities to address issues that affect the quality of their life. VA Organizing emphasizes the participation of those who have traditionally had little or no voice in our society.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:dgooge@mail.umw.edu">Dawn Googe</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:kmarsh@umw.edu">Kristin Marsh</a>(x1501)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Voices for Planned Parenthood (VOX)</td>\r\n<td>VOX works in conjunction with Planned Parenthood to provide safe sex education and easy contraception as well as giving students a chance to lobby for reproductive rights.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:cpickardumw@gmail.com">Claire Pickard\r\n</a><strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:csmith@umw.edu">Connie Smith</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><em>Voices of Praise</em></td>\r\n<td>The purpose of this organization is to promote and cultivate spiritual growth, as well as the promotion of cultural and educational awareness of spiritual music at the University of Mary Washington and in its community.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:tsilver099@gmail.com">Tyshawnda Silver</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:ljohnson@umw.edu">Lori Johnson</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Volleyball (Women)\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59453/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>To create a competitive, fun and team-oriented environment for girls interested in competitive volleyball.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:kkerr@mail.umw.edu">Kylie Kerr</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:jbroome@umw.edu">John Broome</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Volleyball (Co-Ed)\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59468/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>We are a traveling club sport that gives both men and women the opportunity to play competitive volleyball and have fun.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:rkresge@mail.umw.edu">Robin Kresge</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:cemerson@umw.edu">Claudia Emerson</a><strong>\r\n</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><a href="http://wmwc.umwblogs.org/">WMWC Radio Station </a>\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/63059/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>The purpose of the WMWC Radio Station is to train interested Mary Washington community members to provide audio broadcasting entertainment for the Mary Washington community and other interested listeners.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:mpowers@mail.umw.edu">Mike Powers</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:rtuttle@umw.edu">Ray Tuttle</a>(x1660)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Women of Color (WOC)\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59494/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>This club is designed to educate, celebrate, and empower males and females of different races and cultures.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:jrobins5@mail.umw.edu">Jessica Robinson</a>\r\n<a href="mailto:jcook5@mail.umw.edu">Jasmine Cook</a><a href="mailto:WOC@umw.edu%20">\r\n</a><strong>Faculty Advisor:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:grankli@umw.edu">Greta Franklin</a>(x2179)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Wrestling Club\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/64988/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Wrestling Club is a sports club dedicated to wrestling.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:jsmith32@mail.umw.edu">Jared Smith</a><strong>\r\nFaculty Advisor</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:mmermels@umw.edu">Mark Mermelstein</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Yarn Works\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59577/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>Yarn Works is a club devoted to the encouragement of knitting and crocheting, as well as to develop new friendships.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:avercruy@mail.umw.edu">Amanda Vercruysse </a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor: </strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:dodell@umw.edu">Deborah O’Dell</a>(x1417)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><a href="http://youngdemocrats.umwblogs.org/">Young Democrats</a>\r\n<a href="https://orgsync.com/59472/chapter">OrgSync</a></td>\r\n<td>UMW Young Democrats is a group of politically active students dedicated to the goals and principles of the Democratic Party by promoting the interest and understanding of young people in government and the political process. Assisting in elections, political trips, registering students to vote and community service are among our club’s activities.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:ablanck@mail.umw.edu">Ally Blanck</a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:blabrech@umw.edu">Ben LaBreche</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><em>Young Life</em></td>\r\n<td>Young Life is a mission community of Christ-centered adults committed to sharing the message of Jesus Christ with adolescents in the Greater Fredericksburg community. Young Life provides biblical teaching and training toward students who want to become volunteer leaders.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:esmethur@mail.umw.edu">Ellen Smethurst </a>\r\n<strong>Faculty Advisor:</strong>\r\n<a href="mailto:nmyers@umw.edu">H. Nicole Frye Myers </a>(x8026)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8">Young Women’s Leadership Program Club (YWLP)</td>\r\n<td>YWLP provides college students with one-on-one and group mentoring for 7th grade girls in the Fredericksburg Area.</td>\r\n<td bgcolor="#f8f8f8"><strong>Student Contact:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:hcurry@mail.umw.edu">Heather Curry</a><strong>\r\n</strong><strong>Faculty Advisor:\r\n</strong><a href="mailto:dbowen@umw.edu">Dawn Bowen</a>(x1491)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Get Involved', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'get-involved', '', '', '2013-04-22 03:30:30', '2013-04-22 03:30:30', '', 0, 'http://rosemary.umw.edu/~mdunlap/umwsga/wordpress/?page_id=193', 0, 'page', '', 0);
