(277, 1, '2013-03-30 23:57:11', '2013-03-30 23:57:11', '<h1>The SGA Constitution</h1>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nThe SGA Constitution is the governing document of the organization. To read the document click <a href="https://docs.google.com/open?id=0B7h6P4oEiedAcVpWVFFJR04tTEU" target="_blank">here</a>.\r\n\r\nCurrently the student body has the opportunity to vote on suggestions to approve the changes to the SGA Constitution. Some of the changes are minor while others are larger in nature. Please read the proposed changes below and if you have questions and their explanations below and  feel free to contact us at sga@mail.umw.edu.\r\n<h3><b>Article VI. Section 6</b></h3>\r\nAdd the bolded section under the position of President:\r\n<h4>The President shall appoint the SGA Secretary, Treasurer, Executive Coordinator, <b><i>Communications Director, Director of Community Outreach</i></b> and the Technology Coordinator of the Executive Cabinet with the approval of the Student Senate.</h4>\r\n<em>Last year, the Executive Cabinet was expanded to work with the community more and improve communications with students. These changes reflect that expansion.</em>\r\n\r\nRemove the bolded section under the Position of Secretary:\r\n<h4><b><i>The Secretary is responsible for the upkeep of all SGA Bulletin Boards. The Secretary is responsible for all publicity for the SGA. The Secretary shall work with the Senate for publicity reasons whenever necessary.</i></b></h4>\r\n<em>This is a clerical change. These responsibilities have been given to the Communications Director.</em>\r\n\r\nAdd the bolded section under the position of Technology Coordinator:\r\n<h4><b><i>The Technology Coordinator is also responsible for all of the Executive Cabinet’s social media and online presence. </i></b>Rename the Position Director of Communications to <b>Communications Director.</b></h4>\r\nBecause the Communications Director is fairly new, boundaries have to be set to ensure each positions job is clear. The Technology Director will be solely responsible for all digital media while the Communications Director will work on all published “print” media.\r\n\r\n<em>Rewrite the following sentence under Communications Director:</em>\r\n<h4>The <b><i>Communications Director</i> </b>will have the power and responsibility to create and Chair a Communications Committee as directed by the SGA President. The <b><i>Communications Director is responsible for the up keep of all SGA Publicity that is not digital. </i></b><i>The <b>Communications Director </b>shall work with the Senate for publicity reasons whenever necessary.</i></h4>\r\n<h4>Rename the Position of the Involvement and Outreach Coordinator to <b>the Director of Community Outreach.</b></h4>\r\n<em>Remove the bolded statement from the Director of Community Outreach</em>\r\n<h4><b><i>This position will act as a liaison and inform/update the SGA President on the activities of the local city governance. Additionally </i></b>this position is responsible for volunteer participation, including recruitment, supervision and scheduling that involve the local community and Fredericksburg Area.</h4>\r\n<em>This is the LAC Chairs job. This change is clerical in nature.</em>\r\n\r\nAdd the bolded portion to the position description of Director of Community Outreach:\r\n<h4>This position is responsible for volunteer participation, including recruitment, supervision and scheduling that involve the local community and Fredericksburg Area.</h4>\r\n<em>This will allow the Director of Community Outreach to oversee all SGA Community Outreach Projects.</em>\r\n\r\nAdd the bolded portion to the position description of the Director of Community Outreach\r\n<h4>The <b>director</b> will work closely with the <b><i>Communications Director, Executive Coordinator, the Commuter Student Association President and Legislative Action Committee Chair </i></b>in terms of promotion and public relations development through community education, involvement and support. <b><i> </i></b></h4>\r\n<em>This will allow the Director of Community Outreach to oversee all SGA Community Outreach Projects.</em>\r\n<h3><b>Article VI, Section 9</b></h3>\r\nAdd the bolded Section to the removal clause:\r\n<h4>In case of the removal <b><i>or resignation</i></b> of the Judicial Review Board President, Honor Council President, Legislative Action Committee Chairperson, Academic Affairs Council Chairperson, Association of Residence Hals President, Commuting Student Association President or <b><i>Inter-Club Association President </i></b>from office, the power and duties should temporarily to the respective Vice-President or Vice-Chairperson.</h4>\r\n<em>This gives the ICA President instructions incase of the removal or resignation of their President. It also makes accommodations for defines removal and resignation.  </em>\r\n\r\nAdd the bolded Section to Section 13 (to take effect in 2014):\r\n<h4>Elected Executive Cabinet members may not hold positions within Senate or Senate Board, with the Exception of the SGA Vice-President. <b><i>No member of the Executive Cabinet may serve as a member of the Finance Committee (elected or appointed).</i></b><b> </b></h4>\r\n<em>The Finance Committee has been separate from the SGA however, their members are allowed to serve on the committee. By not allowing any member of the Executive Cabinet to serve on the Committee, more students will be granted leadership </em><i>opportunities while keeping Finance Committee completely separate from SGA making it more fair for students. </i>\r\n<h3><b>Article VII, Section 2</b></h3>\r\nRemove the bolded section from Section 2\r\n<h4>The Executive Cabinet shall approve or veto any legislation enacted by the Senate within two weeks,<b><i>lest the legislation is appropriated to the correct body</i></b> or the legislation is automatically vetoed.</h4>\r\n<em>If the Executive Cabinet does not vote in legislation within two weeks it is automatically vetoed, allowing the Senate to override that veto with a 2/3 majority. This is the same as it works in the United States Government.</em>\r\n<h3><b>Article VII, Section 8</b></h3>\r\nAdd the following bolded section to Section 8:\r\n<h4>The Senate Vice-President must be a senator, with at least two consecutive semester of experience as a senator <b><i>(including the semester of elections), </i></b>and shall be elected by his/her fellow senators during the third meeting of the Senate in the Fall Semester and hold no other office within the senate.</h4>\r\n<em>This change allows for the Senate Vice President’s qualification to align with the SGA Vice Presidents qualifications.  </em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '189-revision-3', '', '', '2013-03-30 23:57:11', '2013-03-30 23:57:11', '', 189, 'http://rosemary.umw.edu/~mdunlap/umwsga/wordpress/?p=277', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(278, 1, '2013-04-05 03:17:38', '2013-04-05 03:17:38', '<h1>The SGA Constitution</h1>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nThe SGA Constitution is the governing document of the organization. To read the document click <a href="https://docs.google.com/open?id=0B7h6P4oEiedAcVpWVFFJR04tTEU" target="_blank">here</a>.\r\n\r\nCurrently the student body has the opportunity to vote on suggestions to approve the changes to the SGA Constitution. Some of the changes are minor while others are larger in nature. Please read the proposed changes below and if you have questions and their explanations below and  feel free to contact us at sga@mail.umw.edu.\r\n<h3><b>Article VI. Section 6</b></h3>\r\nAdd the bolded section under the position of President:\r\n<h4>The President shall appoint the SGA Secretary, Treasurer, Executive Coordinator, <b><i>Communications Director, Director of Community Outreach</i></b> and the Technology Coordinator of the Executive Cabinet with the approval of the Student Senate.</h4>\r\n<em>Last year, the Executive Cabinet was expanded to work with the community more and improve communications with students. These changes reflect that expansion.</em>\r\n\r\nRemove the bolded section under the Position of Secretary:\r\n<h4><b><i>The Secretary is responsible for the upkeep of all SGA Bulletin Boards. The Secretary is responsible for all publicity for the SGA. The Secretary shall work with the Senate for publicity reasons whenever necessary.</i></b></h4>\r\n<em>This is a clerical change. These responsibilities have been given to the Communications Director.</em>\r\n\r\nAdd the bolded section under the position of Technology Coordinator:\r\n<h4><b><i>The Technology Coordinator is also responsible for all of the Executive Cabinet’s social media and online presence. </i></b>Rename the Position Director of Communications to <b>Communications Director.</b></h4>\r\nBecause the Communications Director is fairly new, boundaries have to be set to ensure each positions job is clear. The Technology Director will be solely responsible for all digital media while the Communications Director will work on all published “print” media.\r\n\r\n<em>Rewrite the following sentence under Communications Director:</em>\r\n<h4>The <b><i>Communications Director</i> </b>will have the power and responsibility to create and Chair a Communications Committee as directed by the SGA President. The <b><i>Communications Director is responsible for the up keep of all SGA Publicity that is not digital. </i></b><i>The <b>Communications Director </b>shall work with the Senate for publicity reasons whenever necessary.</i></h4>\r\n<h4>Rename the Position of the Involvement and Outreach Coordinator to <b>the Director of Community Outreach.</b></h4>\r\n<em>Remove the bolded statement from the Director of Community Outreach</em>\r\n<h4><b><i>This position will act as a liaison and inform/update the SGA President on the activities of the local city governance. Additionally </i></b>this position is responsible for volunteer participation, including recruitment, supervision and scheduling that involve the local community and Fredericksburg Area.</h4>\r\n<em>This is the LAC Chairs job. This change is clerical in nature.</em>\r\n\r\nAdd the bolded portion to the position description of Director of Community Outreach:\r\n<h4>This position is responsible for volunteer participation, including recruitment, supervision and scheduling that involve the local community and Fredericksburg Area.</h4>\r\n<em>This will allow the Director of Community Outreach to oversee all SGA Community Outreach Projects.</em>\r\n\r\nAdd the bolded portion to the position description of the Director of Community Outreach\r\n<h4>The <b>director</b> will work closely with the <b><i>Communications Director, Executive Coordinator, the Commuter Student Association President and Legislative Action Committee Chair </i></b>in terms of promotion and public relations development through community education, involvement and support. <b><i> </i></b></h4>\r\n<em>This will allow the Director of Community Outreach to oversee all SGA Community Outreach Projects.</em>\r\n<h3><b>Article VI, Section 9</b></h3>\r\nAdd the bolded Section to the removal clause:\r\n<h4>In case of the removal <b><i>or resignation</i></b> of the Judicial Review Board President, Honor Council President, Legislative Action Committee Chairperson, Academic Affairs Council Chairperson, Association of Residence Hals President, Commuting Student Association President or <b><i>Inter-Club Association President </i></b>from office, the power and duties should temporarily to the respective Vice-President or Vice-Chairperson.</h4>\r\n<em>This gives the ICA President instructions incase of the removal or resignation of their President. It also makes accommodations for defines removal and resignation.  </em>\r\n\r\nAdd the bolded Section to Section 13 (to take effect in 2014):\r\n<h4>Elected Executive Cabinet members may not hold positions within Senate or Senate Board, with the Exception of the SGA Vice-President. <b><i>No member of the Executive Cabinet may serve as a member of the Finance Committee (elected or appointed).</i></b><b> </b></h4>\r\n<em>The Finance Committee has been separate from the SGA however, their members are allowed to serve on the committee. By not allowing any member of the Executive Cabinet to serve on the Committee, more students will be granted leadership </em><i>opportunities while keeping Finance Committee completely separate from SGA making it more fair for students. </i>\r\n<h3><b>Article VII, Section 2</b></h3>\r\nRemove the bolded section from Section 2\r\n<h4>The Executive Cabinet shall approve or veto any legislation enacted by the Senate within two weeks,<b><i>lest the legislation is appropriated to the correct body</i></b> or the legislation is automatically vetoed.</h4>\r\n<em>If the Executive Cabinet does not vote in legislation within two weeks it is automatically vetoed, allowing the Senate to override that veto with a 2/3 majority. This is the same as it works in the United States Government.</em>\r\n<h3><b>Article VII, Section 8</b></h3>\r\nAdd the following bolded section to Section 8:\r\n<h4>The Senate Vice-President must be a senator, with at least two consecutive semester of experience as a senator <b><i>(including the semester of elections), </i></b>and shall be elected by his/her fellow senators during the third meeting of the Senate in the Fall Semester and hold no other office within the senate.</h4>\r\n<em>This change allows for the Senate Vice President’s qualification to align with the SGA Vice Presidents qualifications.  </em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n</div>', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '189-revision-4', '', '', '2013-04-05 03:17:38', '2013-04-05 03:17:38', '', 189, 'http://rosemary.umw.edu/~mdunlap/umwsga/wordpress/?p=278', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
