(403, 8, '2013-04-13 01:25:42', '2013-04-13 01:25:42', '<h2><span style="color: #000000; font-size: 16px; font-family: verdana,geneva;">Agenda &amp; Meeting Minutes</span></h2>\r\nOur goal is to have a transparent Student Government. So we post the agenda and minutes online for all to see. Feel free to ask questions or stop by to give your feedback and input. We’d love to hear from you. Click on the links below of the 2012 – 2013 Minutes or the newest agenda. The minutes are updated after they are approved by the Executive Cabinet.\r\n<h2><span style="font-size: 16px; color: #000000; font-family: verdana,geneva;"><strong>THE AGENDA</strong></span></h2>\r\nThe Executive Cabinet of the Student Government Association meets every week at 8PM in Lee 414 to discuss the issues that are paramount to the student body. The agenda is posted weekly here. To get an item on the agenda, please email Monica Chiu (the SGA Secretary) by the Wednesday before the next cabinet meeting. Her email address is mchiu@mail.umw.edu. <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/19-KZAWMYWnq6LFU_jv0q5blENodaH_0ULCo5lKVMe-U/edit" target="_blank">Click here to see the agenda. </a>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #000000;"><strong><span style="font-size: 16px;">THE MINUTES</span></strong></span><br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<p>The Executive Cabinet of the Student Government Association meets every week at 8PM in Lee 414 to discuss the issues that are paramount to the student body. The agenda is posted weekly here. To get an item on the agenda, please email the SGA Secretary, Amanda Motley at amotley@mail.umw.edu, by the Wednesday before the next cabinet meeting. <a href="https://docs.google.com/file/d/0B-1Msni7oztTbEZyc1NUSnE2Ync/edit?usp=sharing"> Click here to see the agenda. </a></p>\r\n<h3>THE MINUTES<img class="alignright  wp-image-2094" title="Cabinet Meeting" alt="" src="http://sga.umw.edu/files/2012/04/CSC_0555-1024x678.jpg" width="394" height="260" /></h3>\r\n<p><a href="https://docs.google.com/open?id=0B7h6P4oEiedASVBiTXVHYlFVSTA" target="_blank">August 27, 2012</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="https://docs.google.com/open?id=0B7h6P4oEiedAaGE3M29Td0tLUk0" target="_blank">September 3, 2012</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="https://docs.google.com/open?id=0B7h6P4oEiedAdExGekpZSHdCLW8" target="_blank">September 10, 2012</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="https://docs.google.com/open?id=0B7h6P4oEiedAcXRxN1hQb1I5a0U" target="_blank">September 17, 2012</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1gTPsptPrajYuRZl0LQZuSZu2DOKb4BHgTj0q8_zYg88/edit" target="_blank">September 24, 2012</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="https://docs.google.com/file/d/0B-1Msni7oztTZVVhZFNCeFEzX1U/edit?usp=sharing">October 1, 2012</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="https://docs.google.com/file/d/0B-1Msni7oztTME55ZmhBOGVCZVk/edit?usp=sharing">October 8, 2012</a></p>\r\n<p>October 15, 2012*</p>\r\n<p><a href="https://docs.google.com/file/d/0B-1Msni7oztTMEVNS3BxUHFwZEk/edit?usp=sharing">October 22, 2012</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="https://docs.google.com/file/d/0B-1Msni7oztTTHRKazNCTXJtdHc/edit?usp=sharing">October 31, 2012</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="https://docs.google.com/file/d/0B-1Msni7oztTd2kwU2hVTGFqZWs/edit?usp=sharing">November 5, 2012</a></p>\r\n<p>November 13, 2012*</p>\r\n<p>November 19, 2012*</p>\r\n<p><a href="https://docs.google.com/file/d/0B-1Msni7oztTRW15NWFzdHBBWDA/edit?usp=sharing">November 26, 2012</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="https://docs.google.com/file/d/0B-1Msni7oztTSEZLN05KNjRHT1k/edit?usp=sharing">December 3, 2012</a></p>\r\n<h3><strong>Spring 2013</strong></h3>\r\n<p><a href="https://docs.google.com/file/d/0B-1Msni7oztTOEM1ZEdTU082ZGM/edit?usp=sharing">January 14, 2013</a></p>\r\n<p>January 28, 2013*</p>\r\n<p><a href="https://docs.google.com/file/d/0B-1Msni7oztTZDVnMVYyVnhuVlU/edit?usp=sharing">February 4, 2013</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="https://docs.google.com/file/d/0B-1Msni7oztTQ2pnOGI4QlFLV1E/edit?usp=sharing">February 11, 2013</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="https://docs.google.com/file/d/0B-1Msni7oztTN01RTjMyT0paVk0/edit?usp=sharing">February 18, 2013</a></p>\r\n<p>February 25, 2013*</p>\r\n<p>March 11, 2013*</p>\r\n<p>March 18, 2013*</p>\r\n<p>March 25, 2013*</p>\r\n<p><a href="https://docs.google.com/file/d/0B-1Msni7oztTMDQxVnhPa3hsR1U/edit?usp=sharing" target="_blank">April 1, 2013</a></p>\r\n<p><a href="https://docs.google.com/file/d/0B-1Msni7oztTU012dmFNcDB1S2c/edit?usp=sharing">April 8, 2013</a></p>', 'Agenda and Meeting Minutes', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '251-revision-15', '', '', '2013-04-13 01:25:42', '2013-04-13 01:25:42', '', 251, 'http://rosemary.umw.edu/~mdunlap/umwsga/wordpress/?p=403', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(405, 8, '2013-04-13 01:29:27', '2013-04-13 01:29:27', '<h1 class="entry-title">The Executive Cabinet</h1>\r\n		\r\n				<div class="entry-content">\r\n			<h5 style="text-align: center;"><strong><strong>Executive Cabinet</strong></strong></h5>\r\n<h5 style="text-align: center;">President:  Stephanie Preston</h5>\r\n<h5 style="text-align: center;">Vice President:  Nate Levine</h5>\r\n<h5 style="text-align: center;">Honor Council President:  Alice O&#8217;Brien</h5>\r\n<h5 style="text-align: center;">Legislative Action Committee Chairperson:  Joe Dolan</h5>\r\n<h5 style="text-align: center;">Association of Residence Halls President: Alyssa Lieurance</h5>\r\n<h5 style="text-align: center;">Commuter Student Association President:  Claire Pickard</h5>\r\n<h5 style="text-align: center;">Academic Affairs Committee Chairperson: Lavar Edmonds</h5>\r\n<h5 style="text-align: center;">Diversity and Unity Coordinating Committee Chair:  Christian Wiedow</h5>\r\n<h5 style="text-align: center;">Inter-Club Association President: Rob Jarvis</h5>\r\n<h5 style="text-align: center;">Judicial Review Board President: Andrew Gabany</h5>\r\n<h5 style="text-align: center;">Executive Coordinator: Samantha Worman</h5>\r\n<h5 style="text-align: center;">Communications Director: Chelsea Kopf</h5>\r\n<h5 style="text-align: center;">Director of Community Outreach: Rad Wan Jarrar</h5>\r\n<h5 style="text-align: center;">Technology Coordinator: Gibran Parvez</h5>\r\n<h5 style="text-align: center;">Treasurer:  Sarah Clay</h5>\r\n<h5 style="text-align: center;">Secretary:   Amanda Motley</h5>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;"><em>The Executive Cabinet represents the student body on all matters that are of concern between the administration and of the student body. The Executive Cabinet is the highest elected body on campus. The members of the Executive Cabinet include voting members and non-voting members. The voting members are: the President, the Vice-President, the Judicial Review Board President, the Honor Council President, the Legislative Action Committee Chairperson, the Academic Affairs Council Chairperson, the Association of Residence Halls President, the Commuting Student Association President, the Diversity and Unity Coordinating Committee Executive Chairperson, the Inter-Club Association President. The Constitutional non-voting members are: the Executive Coordinator, the Director of Community Outreach, the Treasurer, the Secretary, and the Technology Coordinator. Each member of the Executive Cabinet has a full voice at all meetings. Executive Cabinet meetings are open to anyone who would like to participate.</em></p>\r\n		</div>', 'Executive', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '218-revision-4', '', '', '2013-04-13 01:29:27', '2013-04-13 01:29:27', '', 218, 'http://rosemary.umw.edu/~mdunlap/umwsga/wordpress/?p=405', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(406, 1, '2013-04-12 02:33:51', '2013-04-12 02:33:51', '[poll id="2"]', 'Branches', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '190-revision-9', '', '', '2013-04-12 02:33:51', '2013-04-12 02:33:51', '', 190, 'http://rosemary.umw.edu/~mdunlap/umwsga/wordpress/?p=406', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(460, 1, '2013-04-22 02:27:32', '2013-04-22 02:27:32', '<h3><img alt="New Executive Cabinet" src="http://sga.umw.edu/files/2013/02/New-Executive-Cabinet.jpg" width="613" height="234" /></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><span style="font-size: 14px; color: #000000;"><strong>The Student Government Association is here to remind you that your voice matters. </strong></span></h3>\r\nThe SGA is your voice to the administration. We’re here to remind you that your voice matters more than ever. We are a forum where students bring their concerns about campus issues ranging from academics to safety. We address local, state, and national issues which affect students while organizing community events to foster school spirit, and work together to bond the community. SGA Executive Cabinet and Senate Meeting Minutes are updated regularly, please check back for new information. We are so committed to representing you that we even have a representative at every level of the administration… including the Board of Visitors.', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '296-revision-7', '', '', '2013-04-22 02:27:32', '2013-04-22 02:27:32', '', 296, 'http://rosemary.umw.edu/~mdunlap/umwsga/wordpress/?p=460', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
